                <div class="info"> 
                    <h4>What is a SSY Calculator?</h4>
                    A SSY plan calculator works on the following formula -<br><br>
    
                    A = P (1 + r/n) ^ nt.<br><br>
    
                    In the above formula -<br>
                    <ul>
                        <li>A is Compound interest.</li>
                        <li>P is Principle Amount.</li>
                        <li>r is Rate of interest.</li>
                        <li>n is Number of times interest compounds in a year.</li>
                        <li>i is number of years.</li>
                    </ul><br>               
                  
